codex
Patched one concrete migration gap from the refactor plan: the app now hydrates visible sessions through `AppSyncStore`/`SyncNode` instead of waiting for a later push, and permission/question actions now try to load v3 session state before falling back. The changes are in [sync.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/sync/sync.ts#L271), [ops.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/sync/ops.ts#L152), and the regression coverage is in [ops.spec.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/sync/ops.spec.ts#L45).

Verification passed for the touched surface:
`npx vitest run sources/sync/ops.spec.ts`
`yarn typecheck` in `packages/happy-app`
Earlier in this turn, `yarn workspace @slopus/happy-sync test:unit` and `yarn workspace @slopus/happy-sync test:integration` also passed.

This does not finish the entire spec in `happy-sync-major-refactor.md`. The branch still has broader legacy leftovers, especially CLI fallbacks around `ApiSessionClient` and the app’s older sync pipeline. I did not run Level 2/3 flows because they require the real server/LLM/browser harness.
